-- Former General Motors President F. James McDonald Dies at 87, Company Says
-- Vivek Shankar
-- 2010-06-14T23:54:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/f-james-mcdonald-former-president-and-coo-of-general-motors-dies-at-87.html

          
          
             F. James McDonald, who served as
president and chief operating officer of General Motors Corp. in
the 1980s, died yesterday. He was 87.  
 The cause of death wasnâ€™t available, Tom Wilkinson, a
spokesman for the company, now known as General Motors Co., said
in an interview.  
 A former general manager of the Pontiac and Chevrolet
brands, McDonald served as president and operating chief of the
automaker from Feb.1, 1981 to Aug. 31, 1987. He was a graduate
of the General Motors Institute, the precursor of Kettering
University, in Flint, Michigan.  
 McDonald was born on Aug. 3, 1922, in Saginaw, Michigan. He
is survived by his wife of 66 years, Betty; daughter Marybeth
Cunningham; sons John and Tim; seven grandchildren and four
great-grandchildren, according to a statement from GM.  
          
          


  


        